Privacy Policy for Intruguard
Effective Date: 26/02/2026

At Intruguard, we prioritize your privacy. Our application operates on a peer-to-peer basis, meaning no data is collected, stored, or transmitted to any external servers. This Privacy Policy explains how we ensure your privacy and security while using our app.

1. No Data Collection
No Personal Data: We do not collect or store any personal information such as your name, email, or location.
No Server Storage: All communication occurs directly between devices, with no data sent to or stored on any external servers.
No Video or Usage Data: Video streams, control commands, and interactions are confined to the devices involved and are not recorded or transmitted elsewhere.
2. Peer-to-Peer Communication
The app facilitates direct communication between devices, ensuring that your data remains private and secure.
All video feeds, control signals, and location data are exchanged directly between the devices involved in the session.
3. Security and Privacy
Since no data is stored or transmitted to external servers, your privacy is inherently protected.
Communication is secured through device-level security measures, such as encryption, depending on the device and network configuration.
4. Changes to This Privacy Policy
As we do not collect or process any data, this Privacy Policy will remain unchanged unless the app's functionality or data handling practices change. Any updates will be reflected here with an updated effective date.

5. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us from the "Contact" field in the app.





